Press Releases.Title: 623 New Cases of Covid-19 Infection
Press Releases.MainContent:
As of 17 April 2020, 12pm, the Ministry of Health (MOH) has preliminarily confirmed an additional 623 cases of COVID-19 infection in Singapore, the majority of whom are foreign workers in the dormitories.

2.     We are still working through the details of these cases, and further updates will be shared via the MOH press release that will be issued later tonight.
